# Onsite — Supabase connection values
#
# IMPORTANT — read this before assuming this file "just works":
# Onsite is a plain static site (no Vite/Webpack/Node build step), so there
# is no tool here that reads a .env file at build time. This file exists
# purely as a documented REFERENCE for which two values you need and where
# to get them — the app itself reads them from a different, real file:
#
#     js/config/supabaseConfig.js
#
# Copy the two values below into that file's SUPABASE_URL and
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY exports. See SUPABASE_SETUP.md at the project root for
# step-by-step instructions, including exactly where in your Supabase
# dashboard to find these two values, and why the anon key is safe to have
# in a plain text file (it's designed to be public — Row Level Security is
# what actually protects your data, not hiding this key).
#
# Never put your `service_role` key anywhere in this project. That key
# grants full, unrestricted database access and must never appear in any
# file a browser can load — only SUPABASE_URL and the `anon` / `public`
# key belong here.

SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key-here
